obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE BOUNDARY - MARKS, BOMBAY 1 846`
  line `A CT N O. I II OF 1846`
  line `Passed by the Hon’ble the President of the Council of India in Council on the 7 th January`
  line `1846, with the assent of the Right Hon’ble the Governor General of India.`
  line `An Act for the establishment and maintenance of field boundary marks in the Presidency of`
  line Bombay.
  line `W HEREAS it is desirable, with a view to the better definition and security of landed property, the`
  line `prevention of encroachments and disputes, and the identification of lands assessed to, or exempted from,`
  line `the public revenue, that provision should be made for the establishment and maintenance of permanent`
  line `marks to distinguish the b oundaries of fields:`
  line `I. It is hereby enacted, that it shall be lawful, within the territories subject to the Presidency of`
  line `Bombay, for such Revenue Officers as the Governor in Council may entrust with that authority to require`
  line `that marks be erected and maintained by the Owners or Occupants on the boundaries of fields, of such`
  line `materials, and in such number as may appear to such Officers sufficient for permanently distinguishing`
  line `the limits of those fields.`
  line `II. And it is hereby enacted, that the requisition shall be served on the persons owning or occupying`
  line `each field according to the form A. annexed to this Act, and in the event of these persons not being found`
  line `in the Village, that the said requisiti on shall be posted at the Village Chowree or other conspicuous place`
  line `in the Village, which shall be held to be a sufficient service.`
  line `III. And it is hereby enacted, that in default of the Owners or Occupants of the fields complying with`
  line `the requisition, th e said Revenue Officers shall give directions for the erection and repair of such field`
  line `boundary marks, the cost of which shall be equitably apportioned on the fields which they serve to`
  line `distinguish, and shall be charged to the persons possessing a right o f ownership or occupancy in such`
  line `fields, or if there are no such persons forthcoming, to the revenues of the Village in which the fields are`
  line situated.
  line `IV. And it is hereby enacted, that no person being out of possession and claiming a right of ownership`
  line `or occupancy in fields, the cost of erecting or maintaining whose boundary marks has been charged to the`
  line `revenues of the Village, in consequence of his neglecting to defray the same, shall have his claim allowed`
  line `until he makes good all sums so charged.`
  line `V. And it is hereby enacted, that any person who may be convicted of wilfully erasing, removing, or`
  line `injuring field boundary marks, shall be laible to a fine not exceeding Fifty Rupees for each mark so`
  line `erased, removed, or injured, one half of which fine may b e awarded on conviction to the informer, and the`
  line `other half shall be chargeable with the cost of restoring the mark.`
  line `VI. And it is hereby enacted, that authority for the assessment and realization of sums due under the`
  line `provisions of this Act, whether as pr ovide for the erection and maintenance of field boundary marks, and`
  line `shall be exercised by them in conformity with the rules prescribed for the assessment and realization of`
  line `Revenue demands in general, and that the proceedings of those Officers in all such matters shall be`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
